  21 class OpenTests:
  22     def test_open_binary(self):
  23         with resources.open_binary(self.data, 'utf-8.file') as fp:
  24             result = fp.read()
  25             self.assertEqual(result, b'Hello, UTF-8 world!\n')
  26 
  27     def test_open_text_default_encoding(self):
  28         with resources.open_text(self.data, 'utf-8.file') as fp:
  29             result = fp.read()
  30             self.assertEqual(result, 'Hello, UTF-8 world!\n')
  31 
  32     def test_open_text_given_encoding(self):
  33         with resources.open_text(
  34                 self.data, 'utf-16.file', 'utf-16', 'strict') as fp:
  35             result = fp.read()
  36         self.assertEqual(result, 'Hello, UTF-16 world!\n')
  37 
  38     def test_open_text_with_errors(self):
  39         # Raises UnicodeError without the 'errors' argument.
  40         with resources.open_text(
  41                 self.data, 'utf-16.file', 'utf-8', 'strict') as fp:
  42             self.assertRaises(UnicodeError, fp.read)
  43         with resources.open_text(
  44                 self.data, 'utf-16.file', 'utf-8', 'ignore') as fp:
  45             result = fp.read()
  46         self.assertEqual(
  47             result,
  48             'H\x00e\x00l\x00l\x00o\x00,\x00 '
  49             '\x00U\x00T\x00F\x00-\x001\x006\x00 '
  50             '\x00w\x00o\x00r\x00l\x00d\x00!\x00\n\x00')
  51 
  52     def test_open_binary_FileNotFoundError(self):
  53         self.assertRaises(
  54             FileNotFoundError,
  55             resources.open_binary, self.data, 'does-not-exist')
  56 
  57     def test_open_text_FileNotFoundError(self):
  58         self.assertRaises(
  59             FileNotFoundError,
  60             resources.open_text, self.data, 'does-not-exist')
